snippet: The last two Cuban workers at the United States Naval Station at Guantánamo Bay, who kept their jobs even after the relationship between the United States and Cuba soured, retired on Monday.
abstract: Last two Cuban workers at United States Naval Station at Guantanamo Bay retire from jobs they began more than fifty years ago, and kept even after relationship between US and Cuba soured.
lead_paragraph: The last two Cuban workers at the United States Naval Station at Guantánamo Bay, who kept their jobs even after the relationship between the United States and Cuba soured, retired on Monday.

headline.seo: Last 2 Cuban Workers at Guantánamo Bay Retire
headline.main: Cuba: The Sun Sets on a Commuter Era
headline.print_headline: Cuba: The Sun Sets on a Commuter Era
